Hi! My name is Teresa, and I am a Master’s student in Biology specializing in Ecology and Conservation. My research focuses on how the butterfly Euphydryas editha adapts to local altitude and temperature conditions. More broadly, I am interested in how species and natural systems respond and adapt to environmental variation and climate change.

I am passionate about fieldwork and environmental education, and I enjoy exploring ways to communicate ecological research to broader audiences. In my free time, you can usually find me hiking, crocheting, or curled up with a good book.
